Bug report (moq.analyzers issue #981): Three locations in a Roslyn analyzer codebase use string-based name matching instead of symbol-based detection. Example:

```csharp
private static bool IsActionDelegate(INamedTypeSymbol namedType)
{
    return string.Equals(namedType.Name, "Action", StringComparison.Ordinal);
}
```

Files: EventSyntaxExtensions.cs:266-273, LinqToMocksExpressionShouldBeValidAnalyzer (string.Equals on method name 'Of'), SetupShouldNotIncludeAsyncResultAnalyzer (string scan of ReferencedAssemblyNames). The project mandate is symbol-based detection. What is the concrete failure mode and the fix shape?
